Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper focuses on designing high-order finite element discretizations and scalable solvers for the solution of nonlinear incompressible Stokes equations, which is a common problem in computational engineering and science. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a Newton-Krylov method with a block upper triangular preconditioner for the linearized Stokes systems, which is a common topic in numerical analysis. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the implementation of the proposed method and solver, which is relevant to the development of mathematical software. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper uses nonconforming hexahedral meshes and conforming inf-sup stable finite element velocity-pressure pairings, which are topics related to discrete mathematics. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): Although not the main focus of the paper, the topic of ice sheet dynamics may involve visualization and graphics, which could potentially fall under the cs.GR sub-category.
